  <thing id="trkHarrPoi" name="Harrow Points" description="We will be using the Harrow Points listed in the Carrion Crown Players Guide. While the information listed here is the same as what is listed in the Players Guide, I will post it here for easy reference. They are specific to the character, not the player. The cards represent the Fates interjecting on behalf of the character. They will be awarded at the beginning of each new module, and can be used at any time. This is different than the Players Guide that says you can only use 1 per module. You must have the index card to use the ability on the card. If you lose the card, there is no replacement. (Only exception to this will be if the card was just selected and I have not printed a card for it yet.)" compset="Tracker">
    <fieldval field="trkMax" value="6"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Tracker"/>
    <containerreq phase="GlobalTest" priority="0">source.PathCCrown</containerreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="idUmArcCen" name="Rod of the Arcane Cenotaph" description="{b}Description{/b}\nThis rod of ancient stone is inscribed with the personal sigils of dozens of long- dead arcanists, attuning the user to the lingering spiritual vestiges of the dead, allowing him to commune with them and delve their secrets, especially those of a magical nature. The rod grants a +2 bonus to Knowledge checks relating to arcane spellcasters, whether living, dead, or undead. The wielder also gains a +2 bonus to save DCs and caster level checks when casting divination spells relating to dead or undead creatures, and when using {i}augury{/i}, {i}contact other plane{/i}, {i}divination{/i}, or another divination with a percentage chance of success to learn about a dead or undead creature, the user may roll twice and select the better result.\n\nAs a standard action, the rod can be touched to a creature to discern its spellcasting ability (if any) or to an object to discern if it is magical (if so, Spellcraft can be used to identify it), as if using {i}arcane sight{/i}. As a free action, the user may sacrifice one prepared arcane spell or spell slot when making a Knowledge (arcana) or Spellcraft roll in order to gain an insight bonus to the skill check equal to twice the spell&apos;s level.\n\nA {i}rod of the arcane cenotaph{/i} allows the wielder to use {i}speak with dead{/i} (Will DC 14) and {i}vision{/i} once each per day. The rod&apos;s bonus to save DC and caster level checks is doubled when using these powers to learn about arcane spellcasters." compset="Rod" summary="This rod of ancient stone is inscribed with the personal sigils of dozens of long- dead arcanists, attuning the user to the lingering spiritual vestiges of the dead, allowing him to commune with them and delve their secrets, especially those of a magical nature.">
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="13"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="58000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="5"/>
    <usesource source="PathCCrown"/>
    <tag group="iSchool" tag="Divination"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="NoCharge"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iUmRodMoon" name="Rod of the Moon" description="{b}Base Weapon Type:{/b} Mace, Light\n\nThis alchemical silver {i}+1 light mace{/i} glows with a soft silvery light equal to a torch and grants the wielder low-light vision as long as it is in hand. The rod gains the bane property when used as a weapon against lycanthropes. In addition, it can create each of the following magical effects:\n\n{b}{i}Moonglow:{/b}{/i} Once per minute, the rod can limn a single creature within 30 feet with a pale glow like {i}faerie fire{/i} for 1d4 rounds (no save). While so illuminated, the target suffers a -1 penalty to Will saves and to Wisdom and Wisdom-based skill checks.\n\n{b}{i}Moonbeam:{/b}{/i} Once per hour, you can create a 5-foot radius circle of bright light any where within 120 feet. Creatures within the moonbeam are dazzled for 1 minute (DC 14 Reflex negates). Lycanthropes failing their saving throw are fascinated for as long as they remain within the moonbeam. You can redirect the moonbeam anywhere within range as a move action, but if you move more than 120 feet away it winks out immediately. Illumination levels are increased by 1 step within 30 feet of the moonbeam.\n\n{b}{i}Moonstruck:{/b} {/i} Once per day, you can target a creature with {i}moonstruck*{/i} (DC 17). \n{b}*See {i}Advanced Player&apos;s Guide {/i}{/b}" compset="MagicWep" summary="This alchemical silver {i}+1 light mace{/i} glows with a soft silvery light equal to a torch and grants the wielder low-light vision as long as it is in hand.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="33525"/>
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="9"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="3"/>
    <usesource source="PathCCrown"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MagicOnly"/>
    <tag group="IsWeapon" tag="wMaceLight"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Rod"/>
    <tag group="iSchool" tag="Evocation"/>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wMaceLight"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioUmBeyVei" name="Beyonder&apos;s Veil" description="{b}Description{/b}\nThis shimmering translucent veil seems to hold shifting stars within its weave.  The {i}beyonder&apos;s veil{/i} infuses your illusions with the essence of trans-spatial nightmare dimensions beyond the stars. This distorted and disturbing wrongness decreases the save DC to disbelieve your illusions by 1. However, creatures  that fail a saving throw against an illusion spell or spell-like ability you use (other than a save to disbelieve) become shaken for 1 round per level of the spell. If the effect already causes targets to become shaken, this duration stacks with the duration of the effect. Creatures immune to fear are immune to this effect, as are creatures that succeed on their saving throw against your illusions. Creatures with a saving throw bonus specific to fear effects do not apply this bonus to your illusions but are shaken for only half the normal duration." compset="Wondrous" summary="This shimmering translucent veil seems to hold shifting stars within its weave.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="9000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="7"/>
    <usesource source="PathCCrown"/>
