  <thing id="ioUmGauSta" name="Gauntlet of Staveguarding" description="{b}Description{/b}\nThis heavy glove of leather covered in mithral mesh is used to safeguard a rod, staff, or wand from destruction, though it may be used in conjunction with a quarterstaff or with any item or weapon wielded in one hand. The {i}gauntlet of staveguarding{/i} grants a +5 bonus to CMD against disarm and sunder attempts against the held item, and a successful sunder maneuver must first destroy the gauntlet itself (hardness 15, hp 30) before damaging the item being held. A spell targeted at an item in hand (e.g., {i}disintegrate{/i}, {i}heat metal{/i}, {i}shatter{/i}) affects the gauntlet instead; if the gauntlet is destroyed, any leftover damage may affect the item originally targeted.\n\nIf more than one {i}gauntlet of staveguarding{/i} is worn, each must protect a different held item." compset="Wondrous" summary="This heavy glove of leather covered in mithral mesh is used to safeguard a rod, staff, or wand from destruction, though it may be used in conjunction with a quarterstaff or with any item or weapon wielded in one hand.">
