    </thing>
  <thing id="ioUmHeCeSa" name="Helm of Certain Sanity" description="{b}Description{/b}\nCrafted by those who wished to shield their perceptions against mind-bending horrors from beyond, this headgear protects against the loss of mental faculties. Any Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma damage or drain suffered by the wearer is reduced by 2, and the wearer is immune to temporary penalties to these ability scores (e.g., {i}touch of idiocy{/i}). The wearer is also made immune to {i}confusion{/i}, {i}feeblemind{/i}, {i}song of discord{/i}, {i}insanity{/i}, and similar effects and gains a +4 bonus to saving throws against patterns and phantasms.\n\nThese protections come with a price, however, as the {i}helm of certain sanity{/i} also leaves the wearer unable to perceive mythos creatures or spells with the mythos descriptor*, treating them as if they had total concealment at all times. This also makes the wearer immune to gaze attacks or similar sight-based supernatural abilities used by such creatures but also imposes a -20 penalty to Knowledge checks to identify such creatures or their abilities. If the wearer is attacked by a mythos creature or spell*, she can perceive it as if it had concealment, appearing only as a dim, threatening shape, for 1d4 rounds.  \n\n{b}*See the Legendary Games product {i}Tomes of Ancient Knowledge.{/b} {/i}If you are not using that product, Mythos creatures or spells are defined as those that trigger {i}Sanity{/i} checks. See {i}Pathfinder Adventure Path #46: Wake of the Watcher.{/i}" compset="Wondrous" summary="Crafted by those who wished to shield their perceptions against mind-bending horrors from beyond, this headgear protects against the loss of mental faculties.">
