  <thing id="ioUmSeaCan" name="S&#233;ance Candle" description="{b}Description{/b}\nUsually dead black or bone white, a {i}s&#233;ance candle{/i} burns for 1 hour. While alight, it attracts the lingering vestiges of dead spirits to come and whisper to the living or provide clues to answer their questions when they meditate upon the desired information in the light of the candle, depending on the amount of time spent.\n\n{b}10 Minutes:{/b} +2 insight bonus to a Knowledge check to learn about a specific named individual (who may be living, dead, or undead) or to a Diplomacy check to gather information about an individual or when interacting with a sentient undead creature. This bonus is doubled if the {i}s&#233;ance candle{/i} is burned at a creature&apos;s grave site or in its current or former home. This bonus does not stack with itself; each time this ability is used, it must apply to a different Knowledge or Diplomacy check.\n\n{b}20 Minutes:{/b} Ask a single question of a corpse, as {i}speak with dead{/i} (Will DC 14) or perform an {i}augury{/i} related to a specific named individual.\n\n{b}60 minutes:{/b} Perform a {i}divination{/i} related to a specific named individual.\n\nIf a haunt is present when a {i}s&#233;ance candle{/i} is lit, any creature within 5 feet of the candle gains +2 bonus to skill checks to notice or interact with the haunt; however, the candle enables to the haunt to manifest more fully, and save DCs against it are increased by 1 within 5 feet of the {i}s&#233;ance candle{/i}. If the {i}s&#233;ance candle{/i} is extinguished prematurely, 10 minutes of its burning time is wasted but no benefit is gained.\n\n{b}Note{/b}: Each usage on the in-play tab represents 10 minutes of burning time is used." compset="Wondrous" summary="Usually dead black or bone white, a {i}s&#233;ance candle{/i} burns for 1 hour.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="1500"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="7"/>
