  <thing id="ioUmEldTal" name="Elder Talisman" description="{b}Description{/b}\nThis rough-hewn stone in the form of a seven-pointed star at first appears a weathered relic of ancient times, but a close inspection reveals spidery whorls and traceries of pictographic runes that bend the mind and yet all lead back into the heart of the star. A creature carrying an {i}elder talisman{/i} gains spell resistance of 30 and the effect of a double-strength {i}protection from evil{/i}, though these protections apply only against creatures or effects with the mythos descriptor (regardless of alignment).*\n\nIf the {i}elder talisman{/i} is held in both hands, the bearer may {i}detect mythos{/i} at will as a standard action, and may also trigger each of the following powers once per day: {i}dispel mythos{/i}, {i}magic circle against mythos{/i}, or {i}shield of mythos{/i}. These spells function as {i}detect evil{/i}, {i}dispel evil{/i}, {i}magic circle against evil{/i}, and {i}shield of law{/i}, but they function against mythos creatures and spells (regardless of alignment).*\n\nInimical to mythos creatures,* an {i}elder talisman{/i} enhances {i}binding{/i}, {i}dimensional anchor{/i}, {i}dimensional lock{/i}, {i}forbiddance{/i}, and any spell that would force them to return to their home plane (e.g., {i}banishment{/i}, {i}dismissal{/i}, {i}holy word{/i}), increasing the save DC against such effects by +2 and caster level checks to overcome SR by +4.  \n\nFinally, an {i}elder talisman{/i} is impervious to damage from any mythos spell or creature,* whether from physical or magical attacks. Any non-damaging spell or effect used by a mythos creature* to suppress or circumvent the power of an {i}elder talisman{/i} has no effect on it or any magical effect it produces, even spells such as {i}antimagic field{/i}, {i}mage&apos;s disjunction{/i}, and {i}wish{/i}. An {i}elder talisman{/i} can be used as the focus for a permanent magical effect such as {i}forbiddance{/i} or {i}hallow{/i}; if this is done, that spell becomes impervious to {i}dispelling{/i} or {i}suppression{/i} by mythos spells or creatures.* In addition, that spell&apos;s effects (or those of a companion spell tied to {i}hallow{/i}) are doubled (if a static bonus) or empowered (if a variable numeric effect). It may serve as the focus for only one spell at a time; if physically removed from the spell&apos;s area of effect, its enhancement to that spell is ended.\n\n{b}Destruction\nRequirements{/b} An {i}elder talisman{/i} can be destroyed by a {i}rod of cancellation{/i} that is held simultaneously by creatures with overwhelming auras {i}(Pathfinder RPG Core Rulebook{/i} 266) of law, chaos, evil, and good, or if struck by weapons or spells with the chaotic, evil, good, and lawful descriptors for at least 50 points of damage of each type within a single round.\n\n{b}*See the Legendary Games product {i}Tomes of Ancient Knowledge.{/b} {/i}If you are not using that product, Mythos creatures or spells are defined as those that trigger {i}Sanity{/i} checks. See {i}Pathfinder Adventure Path #46: Wake of the Watcher.{/i}" compset="Wondrous" summary="This rough-hewn stone in the form of a seven-pointed star at first appears a weathered relic of ancient times, but a close inspection reveals spidery whorls and traceries of pictographic runes that bend the mind and yet all lead back into the heart of the star." uniqueness="unique">
