  <thing id="iUmMitBlad" name="Mitra&apos;s Blade" description="{b}Base Weapon Type:{/b} Greatsword\n\n{b}Price:{/b} These are unique items and there for have no price.  Should you decide, of your own free will, not to keep the item, it returns to where it came from.\n\n{b}Notes:{/b} Any spell-like abilities gained through the use of this legendary weapon are based on the wielder&apos;s highest mental characteristic (Int, Wis, or Cha).  The caster level required for any effects of the legendary weapon are based on the wielder&apos;s total Hit Dice.  Any reference to level on an ability refers to the items level, not the wielders level.\n\n{b}Requirements:{/b} In order to bond with the weapon and allow it to level with you, you must have a minimum base attack bonus of 3.  In order for you to overcome the jealousy of the weapon, you must have the Quick Draw and Weapon Focus (Greatsword) Feats.\n\nSaid to be a shard of sunlight made solid, {i}Mitra&apos;s Blade{/i} was forged in kiln of the sun god&apos;s temple at the time-lost oasis of Siwath. Once a millennium, in an event called the Day of Eternal Night, the lord of darkness wages a battle against life and light. During this time the sun cannot rise and the undead walk the land. It is said just before each Day of Eternal Night a warrior appears to take up {i}Mitra&apos;s Blade{/i} against the swarming, undead hordes. Prophecy also indicates if no warrior emerges to defend the temple at Siwath, the lord of darkness will rule the earth for eternity.\n\n{i}Mitra&apos;s Blade{/i} is a greatsword. {b}{u}The curved blade glows with light at all times despite what the wielder wishes.{/u}{/b} The pommel sports a bright red ruby and the hilt is a half-circle said to symbolize the rising sun.  Wielders strike with the speed of sunlight and eventually gain the gift of prophecy. The sword is also particularly attuned to destroying undead, and deals extra damage against them." compset="MagicWep" summary="Said to be a shard of sunlight made solid, {i}Mitra&apos;s Blade{/i} was forged in kiln of the sun god&apos;s temple at the time-lost oasis of Siwath." uniqueness="unique">
